# Assets & Paths

## WHEN TO USE
- Working with geospatial datasets (GADM, Biome, Phenology)
- Running segmentation or metadata extraction
- Troubleshooting missing data/files

## Canonical Paths (inside containers)
- GADM: `/app/assets/gadm/gadm_410.gpkg`
- Phenology: `/app/assets/pheno/modispheno_aggregated_normalized.zarr`
- Biome: `/app/assets/biom/terres_ecosystems.gpkg`
- Models: `/app/assets/models/segformer_b5_full_epoch_100.safetensors`

## Settings (Python)
- Use `from shared.settings import settings`
- Derive directories from:
  - `settings.base_path`
  - `settings.processing_path`
  - `settings.archive_path`, `settings.cog_path`, `settings.thumbnail_path`
  - `settings.user_label_path`, `settings.trash_path`, `settings.downloads_path`, `settings.raw_images_path`
- Table names: `settings.<...>_table` properties

## Asset Setup
```bash
make download-assets
make symlinks  # creates legacy symlinks for tests
```

## Common Pitfalls
- Do not hardcode host paths; rely on `settings` and Compose volume mounts
